      }
    },
    {
      "id": "legend-type-walkthrough-step-1",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Step 1",
      "position": {
        "x": -260,
        "y": 40
      },
      "width": 520,
      "height": 260,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "## Step 1: Build a catalog graph\n\nIn a separate graph (the catalog), add `bridge` nodes that target node classes.\n\nEach bridge should set:\n- `target.kind = node-class`\n- `target.key` (stable type key)\n- `target.meaning` (why this type exists)\n\nExpected:\n- [ ] Catalog graph contains 2+ node-class bridge targets\n- [ ] Keys are stable and meaningful"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "legend-type-walkthrough-step-2",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Step 2",
      "position": {
        "x": -260,
        "y": 330
      },
      "width": 520,
      "height": 260,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "## Step 2: Import the catalog in a consumer graph\n\nIn the consumer graph, add a `bridge` node pointing at the catalog graph ref.\n\nImportant:\n- The consumer bridge must include `create` in grants.\n\nExpected:\n- [ ] Legend tab shows the catalog node classes\n- [ ] Clicking + spawns nodes"
      }
    },
